# https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=woIkysZytSs

(https://google.github.io/styleguide/pyguide.html)

- style guide for google python libraries

1. Imports

- no wildcards
- import the module, not the function


2. use main function

- __name...


3. comprehensions

- only use simple comprehensions (max one line per part), for more complicated cases — use a for loop

4. default function argument

- don't use too many arguments
- don't use mutable default arguments

5. properties

- getting or setting instance variables that require trivial calculations
- use getter or setter if they are more advanced

6.

7. lexical scope

8. exception handling

- if you can't do anything useful with the error, don't catch it and let some other part of the program handle it

8.1. asserts

- use asserts to ensure internal correctness, not to ensure correct usage of this code — raise exceptions instead
- don't use catchall
